    <!-- My Experience -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-indigo-50 to-purple-50 border-[3px] border-indigo-300 p-6 md:p-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">My Experience: The $6/Month Difference That Changed Everything</h2>
        <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-6 uppercase tracking-wider font-bold">Real testing, not theoretical comparison</p>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">A solopreneur launching a digital course needed a landing page. Budget was tightâ€”every dollar mattered. Same offer, tested both builders.</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed"><strong>Framer route:</strong> Generated in 2 minutes. Spent 45 minutes customizing the designâ€”adding a gradient hero, testimonials slider, FAQ accordion. Looked stunning. Loaded in 0.7 seconds. Cost: $15/month.</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed"><strong>Mixo route:</strong> Generated in 47 seconds. Spent 20 minutes tweaking content. Looked professional and clean. Loaded in 1.1 seconds. Cost: $9/month.</p>
          <div class="bg-indigo-100 border-l-[4px] border-indigo-500 p-4 my-4">
            <p class="text-sm text-indigo-900 font-medium"><strong>90-day A/B test:</strong> Split traffic 50/50. Framer site had 3,400 visitors, 218 email signups, 12 course purchases ($497 each) = $5,964 revenue. Mixo site had 3,300 visitors, 204 signups, 11 purchases = $5,467 revenue. Framer generated $497 more. But Framer cost $15/mo Ã— 3 = $45 vs Mixo's $9 Ã— 3 = $27. Net difference: $479.</p>
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed"><strong>The brutal truth:</strong> Framer's superior design converted 7% better. But the difference was $479 over 3 months on a $6,000 revenue test. For a solopreneur just starting, that $6/month savings with Mixo meant earlier reinvestment in ads. For an established brand, Framer's design edge pays for itself 100x over.</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed"><strong>But then scenario #2:</strong> A designer building their portfolio. Visual showcase mattersâ€”everything. Clients judge your design skills BY your design.</p>
          <div class="bg-purple-100 border-l-[4px] border-purple-500 p-4 my-4">
            <p class="text-sm text-purple-900 font-medium"><strong>The portfolio reality:</strong> Framer portfolio landed 4 new clients in first month ($12,000 in projects). Mixo portfolio (tested for 2 weeks) landed 1 client ($3,000). Framer's design superiority directly impacts design professionals' revenue. Mixo can't compete for visual-first businesses.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-violet-100 border-l-[4px] border-violet-500 p-4 my-4">
            <p class="text-sm text-violet-900 font-medium"><strong>The lesson:</strong> Framer for designers, portfolios, startups, anything visual. Mixo for small business, lead gen, MVP testing, budget-conscious launches. The $6/month is trivial if design affects your revenue. It's significant if you're just starting and need every dollar for growth.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Deep Dive -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">The Key Differences</h2>

      <div class="mb-8">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Design Philosophy</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">
